<dl id="n35215d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n35" href="#n35215d">N35 (VI.B.24)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n35all.htm#n35215d"> 215(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> ihram / (dress) / labbeyka</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[<i>The Ceremonies and Merwa</i>.&mdash; [&hellip;]</font>The pilgrim enters the Haram in the antique and scanty pilgrimage dress (ihram) <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> His devotion is expressed in shouts of &ldquo;Labbeyka&rdquo; (a word of obscure origin and meaning; <small> &ldquo;MECCA&rdquo; <a name="EBMC" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#EBMC"><cite title="source">Encyclopaedia Britannica</cite></a>, 11th edit. (1911) 954</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
